<Project>

  <!--
    Documented C1 canonical deviation for DbContextBuilder.

    The canonical fleet baseline drops tests/Directory.Build.props so test
    projects inherit TreatWarningsAsErrors=true (Release) from the root
    Directory.Build.props — holding tests to the same bar as src code.

    DbContextBuilder cannot meet that bar today because the test projects
    `<Compile>`-link the EF-scaffolded AdventureWorks model files (under
    extra-projects/AdventureWorks-EF6/Models/Generated/*.cs and the EF7
    equivalent). Those generated files trip thousands of analyzer warnings
    (MA0051 method-too-long, MA0003 name-the-parameter, CS8669 nullable-
    annotation-outside-context, CS1591 missing-XML-doc) that are not
    DbContextBuilder bugs — they are EF scaffolder output.

    Until issue #235 closes (re-scaffold the AdventureWorks models with a
    modern `dotnet ef dbcontext scaffold` toolchain that emits `#nullable
    enable` + `<auto-generated>` headers, then close test-XML-doc gaps),
    this file restores `<TreatWarningsAsErrors>false</TreatWarningsAsErrors>`
    on the tests/ subtree only.

    Once #235 lands, this file should be deleted so DbContextBuilder
    rejoins the canonical Option-A standard.
  -->

  <Import Project="$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)..\Directory.Build.props" />

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TreatWarningsAsErrors>false</TreatWarningsAsErrors>
  </PropertyGroup>

</Project>
